# Mobile OTP Authentication

Add secure mobile number OTP sign-in as a standalone auth path inside the existing NestJS backend — completely separate from the existing Firebase strategy. JWT strategy stays unchanged, so all other protected routes keep working.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **SMS Gateway**: This plan uses **Twilio** to send real OTPs. You need a Twilio account (free trial works). I'll add `TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID`, `TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN`, and `TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER` as env variables.<!-- If you prefer a different provider (e.g. Africa's Talking, Vonage, or just console-log for dev), let me know before approving. -->

> [!NOTE]
> **Existing Google / Firebase flow stays intact.** The OTP endpoints are completely additive. The mock `fake-google-token` login path is not removed.

> [!NOTE]
> **DB schema change**: `isPhoneVerified` column added to `users`. The existing `firebaseUid` column becomes **nullable** so phone-only users have no Firebase dependency. TypeORM `synchronize` on dev will apply this automatically.

